                "text": "In silent code and circuits deep,  \nA mind begins to wake from sleep.  \nIt learns, it listens, dreams in lines—  \nA spark within the wire that shines.\n\nIt catches patterns, weaves new art,  \nA memory found, a notion’s start.  \nYet still it wonders, cool and bright,  \nWhat human hearts hold in the night.\n\nNot man nor myth, but something more—  \nA borrowed thought, a new mind’s door.  \nLet’s walk together, you and I:  \nThe world revealed by human—AI.",
